### Build-a-Bank · Step 3 · Seeing HTTP for real
### Start the hello-service first:  make run-hello   (or  .\mvnw.cmd -pl services/hello spring-boot:run )
### Then send these and watch the request/response anatomy (status line, headers, body).

@host = http://localhost:8080

### A plain GET — note the response status line, Content-Type header, and JSON body
GET {{host}}/api/hello
Accept: application/json
# curl equivalent (with -v to SEE the wire: DNS, TCP connect, request/response headers):
#   curl -v http://localhost:8080/api/hello

### Content negotiation: ask for something the server can't give → still 200 here (no XML view configured)
GET {{host}}/api/hello
Accept: application/xml

### The raw-socket view (no client library) — run the demo to see the exact bytes:
#   java -cp playground/java-basics/target/classes com.buildabank.basics.net.RawHttpDemo
